    "title": "LED Bar Brightness Comparison",
    "description": "Three LEDs in a row share USB power; each branch has its own resistor (150Ω, 470Ω, 1kΩ). All light at once — red is brightest on the left, green is medium, blue is dimmest on the right. Compare the steps like a brightness bar (not a pot that turns them on one by one)."
